title: For Sale/Trade:  gen 3 Glock 21 SF (short frame) with night sights 4/13 round mags
postcontent: This is a gen 3 glock 21 sf which has a reduced, much more manageable grip than the standard glock 21 grip. This gun has meprolight night sights, a 3.5lb trigger and 4 13 round mags. This gun is used but in great shape. I love this gun but its time for something new. Of the 30 some glocks I've owned in my life this one is the most accurate and fun to shoot, it even consistently outshoots my buddies HK USP. I really hate to get rid of it but its time for someone else to enjoy it and for me to enjoy something new. This glock is somewhat rare in that it has the now discontinued ambi mag release. I guess a few of them had problems so glock discontinued them. Ive never had any troubles with the mag release, I see it as a future collector, the cool thing about the rare ambi mag release 21's is that glock will swap it out for a brand new gen 3 frame at no cost so at anypoint you could send the frame to glock and have a new one to replace it. This one doesn't have much ware so I'm waiting till it has been used a lot more to redeem the new frame. Im looking to trade for a used, midgrade ar-15 like a bushmaster or palmetto state armory just to name a couple brands that are cheaper on the used market. I don't care about barrel length but I would like to at least be threaded. I prefer flat top (A3} upper receivers but I'm ok with an {A2} fixed upper. No cheapo plastic ar-15 lowers please.

postcontent:
*MATCHING VET BRINGBACK* 1939 K98 Mauser 8MM "27" Code

This is as original as it gets. Completely matching and unmolested 1939 date 27 code K98 Mauser with low serial number 194i. This is original down to the L&F 1939 dated sling, and even have the original cleaning kit issued with the gun in its original leather pouch. Also comes with a factory 1939 8mm ammo box.
Code 27 was formerly S27, which stood for Erfurter Maschinenfabrik (Erma). The receiver, barrel, rear sight group, bolt group including firing pin, bolt release, floor plate assembly, follower, trigger group screws, bands, bayonet lug, and stock are all matching. The stock has not been sanded and has an original K98K sling marked 1939 with maker.
The bore is excellent with no import mark on the barrel and the stock has not been cut. Still has most of the finish except for the butt plate. Erma stopped production of the K98K in 1941, and the serial number of this rifle is #194, making it a fairly early, hard to find variant.

The gun is all matching down to the screws, and cleaning rod. Nothing has been altered or changed since it left the field. Has the original blueing and is in excellent shape.
Gun has all birds intact and no import or Russian marks.

1932 Tula 
Hex receiver
Ex dragoon means it was originally a 91/dragoon/Cossack and they reconfigured them to 91/30 specs. Meaning different rear and front sights, and the fact that they are 2" shorter than 91/30. postcontent:
Great Fish & Ski Boat at a Great Price! This boat has a really good layout for Fishing, Cruising, Skiing or Tubing.

The Boat:
-	Scoot across the lake in this beautiful metallic black and silver 1998 ProCraft 215 SuperCombo with a 2004 250HP Electronic Fuel Injected Mercury outboard motor. This motor has had minimal usage since being installed in 2007 and has the power you need to get across the lake or to pull a skier or tube. You have a choice of props, from a 5 bladed "High 5" prop that provides really solid hole shot power to a 4 bladed "Tempest" for good low-end power with and a higher top-end than the "High 5". Both props are stainless steel and have zero defects. Relax and sit back while moving from spot to spot on the lake or pulling a tube or skier, there is ample and comfortable seating for 7 (three across back row, driver, co-pilot and two on the front) and you can keep drinks and food chilly with a built in cooler. Hey, while having a frosty beverage you can crank up the tunes on the (1 year old) marine stereo system with CD, Blue Tooth and USB capability. Tunes and beverage make you want to dance (just kidding)? The deck area makes moving about easy and provides a lot of open space. Whoa, starting to rain, wanting to catch some Zzzz's or maybe a little too sunny outside, throw on the included water proof cover or the removable bimini top and enjoy.
As a Skiing or Tubing Boat:
-	Mount the removable competition ski pole (really cool and rock solid), hook-up the ski rope and you are ready to go in a couple of minutes. Front and back decks for lounging and watching the action, room for seven passengers, ski and lifejacket storage lockers as well as three storage lockers up front, built in cooler, stow-away/easy access ladder to using when boarding from land or water and a GPS unit to bring you home.

As a Fishing Boat:

-	Attach the removable pedestal seats (one front and one back), turn on the GPS/Fish Locator and fire up the 250 to get to your favorite fishing spot. Once you are there, attach the 24V MotorGuide trolling motor (easy in and out of the water with a quick release mount), turn on the two aerated live wells and fish locator and have at it. All fished out and ready to leave! There is plenty of space to store things (two storage lockers as well three storage lockers up front and a built in cooler). Use the two-bank, MotorGuide battery charger to charge the batteries. It's as simple as plugging an extension cord into an outlet, no more hooking a battery charger up.

The Trailer:

-	ProCraft factory tandem axle trailer with five, one year old tires, surge breaks (units were replaced 6 years ago), carpeted bunks and these really cool jack stands (all you have to do is drop them, back-up a foot or so and the trailer is raised to the point that you can either take pressure off the tires for storage or change a flat).

General:	

-	This boat has really never given me a problem. I am meticulous in its up keep, always running premium fuel (only requires mid-grade) and oil (Mercury Quicksilver Premium Synthetic) treated with Mercury Quicksilver Fuel Treatments, storing covered in my driveway or in a garage. It has always been pulled from the water and cleaned after use and never run in salt water. The hull keeps you from getting hammered when the water conditions are less than desirable and the power steering makes turning a breeze.
-	Also included several life jackets, three new batteries (two for trolling motor and one for accessories), ski/tow rope, several docking bumpers, anchor and maybe a towable tube.
-	This boat is loaded with every option available at the time it was manufactured and if you are looking for a boat that you can do some serious fishing with or to take out cruising, skiing or tubing this is your boat. Offered at $9,000. Contact me with questions or to see the boat. The only reason that I am selling is because I only use it three or four times a year and do not see use increasing anytime soon. Private seller and no trade offers please.

title: For Sale:  FRANCHI SPA 12
postcontent:
This shotgun  is in mint condition with hardly any rounds fired , it was manufactured in 1982.
I will consider partial trades on .45 auto hi-cap handguns, Mossberg 930 tactical shotgun, AK-47, AR 15. PLEASE CALL REDACTED 

The Franchi SPAS-12 is a combat shotgun manufactured by Italian firearms company Franchi from 1979 to 2000. Production stopped fully in the year 2000 meaning there are currently no SPAS shotguns being produced. Only five percent (about 1,850) of the estimated Franchi SPAS 12 shotguns manufactured were imported into the United States. The SPAS-12 is a dual-mode shotgun, adjustable for semi-automatic or pump-action operation. The SPAS-12 was sold to military and police users worldwide on the civilian market, and has been featured in many movies, TV shows and video games.[1]

The appearance and intended purpose of the SPAS-12 initially led to its "Military" designation as a Combat Shotgun. The SPAS-12 was designed from the ground up as a rugged military shotgun and it was named the Special Purpose Automatic Shotgun. In 1990 Franchi renamed the shotgun to the Sporting Purpose Automatic Shotgun, this allowed continued sales to the United States as a limited-magazine-capacity, fixed-stock model until 1994. Following the United States Federal Assault Weapons Ban, imports of SPAS-12 shotguns were stopped into the United States. In September 2004 the ban had expired, but Franchi had ended production in 2000 of the SPAS-12 . The SPAS-12's retail price in its final year of 2000 was $1500.00 USD averaged for final sales outside the United States to non-restricted countries. Franchi S.p.A. Italy
